{{Malay name|Adee Suhardee|Muhidin}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Adee Suhardee | fullname = Haji Adee Suharde bin Haji Muhidin | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1979|9|26|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Brunei]] | height = | position = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Kasuka FC]] (team manager) | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2015| caps1 = | goals1 = | clubs1 = [[Kasuka FC]] | nationalyears1= 2001 | nationalcaps1= 6 | nationalgoals1= 0 | nationalteam1= [[Brunei national football team|Brunei]] | nationalyears2= 2001 | nationalcaps2= 2 | nationalgoals2= 0 | nationalteam2= [[Brunei national under-23 football team|Brunei U23]] | manageryears1 = 2018– | managerclubs1 = [[Kasuka FC]] (team manager) | club-update = 19 March 2018 | ntupdate = 19 March 2018 }}
[[Ustaz]] '''Haji Adee Suharde bin Haji Muhidin''' (born 26 September 1979) is a [[Brunei]]an former international [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a midfielder. He is currently team manager of [[Kasuka FC]] of the [[Brunei Super League]].<ref name="mp">{{cite web |title=Indera SC mara ke suku akhir|url=https://mediapermata.com.bn/indera-sc-mara-ke-suku-akhir/|date=8 March 2018|publisher=Media Permata|accessdate=13 March 2018}}</ref>
Adee played as a Brunei youth international in the late nineties, and was selected for the [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC First Round#Group 8|2002 FIFA World Cup qualifying matches]] from April to May in 2001 at the age of 21.<ref>{{cite web |title=Football - Brunei soccer teams unveiled|url=http://www.e-borneo.com/cgi-bin/np/viewnews.cgi?category=2&id=986357099|date=4 April 2001|publisher=Borneo Bulletin|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> He made his full Brunei debut against Yemen as a late substitute for [[Rosanan Samak]] in a 0-5 loss. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=3848/match=20922/index.html|title=2002 FIFA World Cup Korea/Japan ? Preliminaries Brunei Darussalam - Yemen |publisher=FIFA.com|date=|deadurl= |archiveurl=|archivedate=|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> He went on to start four of the six qualifying games which all ended in defeats.<ref>{{cite web |title=India wins as expected, but second place eludes|url=http://www.thehindu.com/2001/05/21/stories/07210441.htm|date=21 May 2001|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> He was also with the [[Brunei national under-23 football team|Brunei under-23 team]] that participated in the [[2001 Southeast Asian Games|21st SEA Games]], featuring for the Young Wasps twice against [[Vietnam national under-23 football team|Vietnam]] and [[Indonesia national under-23 football team|Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=South East Asian Games 2001 (Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia) - Match Details|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/sea01-det.html|date=20 September 2001|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref>
Adee however subsequently focused on his studies, pursuing a career as an [[Islamic studies|Islamic religious education]] officer. He graduated from [[Universiti Brunei Darussalam]] in 2004, and taught at schools namely SR Lamunin, [[Sayyidina Abu Bakar Secondary School|SM Sayyidina Abu Bakar]] and [[Raja Isteri Pengiran Anak Damit Girls' Arabic Religious Secondary School|SUAMPRI Pengiran Anak Damit]].<ref>https://www.linkedin.com/in/hj-adee-suhardee-hj-muhidin-1522b75a</ref>
[[Kasuka FC]], a team that withdrew from the [[2007-08 Brunei Premier League]], reformed in 2014 and entered the [[Brunei Premier League]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=Titleholders no problem with postponement|url=http://bruneifootball.blogspot.com/2015/02/titleholders-no-problem-with.html|date=6 February 2015|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> Adee was registered as a player in that season,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst-premierleague-2015-teams-03.htm|title=KASUKA FOOTBALL CLUB|publisher=National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|date=|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411190510/http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst-premierleague-2015-teams-03.htm|archivedate=11 April 2015|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> and celebrated promotion to the [[Brunei Super League]] by finishing in third place ([[Tabuan Muda|Tabuan U18]] in second place could not be promoted).<ref>{{cite web |title=MS ABDB open campaign with victory|url=http://msabdbft.blogspot.com/2016/03/ms-abdb-open-campaign-with-victory_14.html|date=14 March 2016|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref> He was appointed team manager in 2018.<ref name="mp" />
