{{Unreferenced|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox ski jumping hill | hill_name = Bolleberget | nickname = | image = | caption = | location = | city = [[Bollnäs]] | country = [[Sweden]] | opened = 1964 | renovated = 1995 | expanded = | closed = 2001 | demolished = | size = | k-spot = K-90, K-60, K-40, K-20 | hill size = | hill record = | championships = | olympics = | world championships = }} '''Bolleberget''' are [[ski jumping]] hills in [[Bollnäs]], [[Sweden]].
==History== It was opened in 1964 and owned by Bollnäs GoIF, and closed in 2001. It hosted one [[Fédération Internationale de Ski|FIS]] [[Ski jumping World Cup]] event in 1991 on normal hill.
