{{use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = IRQ | NOCname = [[National Olympic Committee of Iraq]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1968 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.iraqiolympic.org }}&nbsp;{{ar icon}} | location = [[Mexico City]] | competitors = 3 | sports = 3 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Iraq]]''' competed at the '''[[1968 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]. Three competitors, all men, took part in four events in three sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/IRQ/summer/1968/ |title=Iraq at the 1968 Mexico City Summer Games |accessdate=7 September 2014 |work=sports-reference.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025142605/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/IRQ/summer/1968/ |archivedate=25 October 2014 |df= }}</ref>
==Cycling== {{main|Cycling at the 1968 Summer Olympics}} One cyclist represented Iraq in 1968.
;[[Cycling at the 1968 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|Individual road race]] * [[George Artin]] &mdash; DNF (→ no ranking)
==Weightlifting== {{main|Weightlifting at the 1968 Summer Olympics}}
'''Lightweight''' * [[Zuhair Mansoor]] :* Press &mdash; 122.5 kg :* Snatch &mdash; 110.0 kg :* Jerk &mdash; 155.0 kg :* ''Total'' &mdash; 387.5 kg (→ 11th place)
==Wrestling== {{main|Wrestling at the 1968 Summer Olympics}}
'''Men's Greco-Roman featherweight (63&nbsp;kg)''' * [[Ismail Al Karaghouli]] :* Round 1 &mdash; fought [[Roman Rurua]] of the [[USSR at the 1968 Summer Olympics|USSR]] :* Round 2 &mdash; DNS
'''Men's freestyle featherweight (63&nbsp;kg)''' * [[Ismail Al Karaghouli]] :* Round 1 &mdash; fought [[José García (wrestler)|José García]] of [[Guatemala at the 1968 Summer Olympics|Guatemala]] :* Round 2 &mdash; fought [[Todorov Enio]] of [[Bulgaria at the 1968 Summer Olympics|Bulgaria]] :* Round 3 &mdash; fought [[José Ramos (wrestler)|José Ramos]] of [[Cuba at the 1968 Summer Olympics|Cuba]] :* Round 4 &mdash; fought [[Jozsef Rusznyak]] of [[Hungary at the 1968 Summer Olympics|Hungary]]
