{{Infobox football biography |name = Kenny Kunst |image = |caption = |fullname = Kenneth Jesus Gregorio Kunst |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|11|01|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Willemstad, Curaçao|Willemstad]], Curaçao |height = {{height|m=1.75}} |position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] |currentclub = [[RKSV Centro Dominguito|Centro Dominguito]] |clubnumber = |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = 2004–2006 |clubs1 = [[S.V. Victory Boys|Victory Boys]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 2006–2007 |clubs2 = [[Centro Social Deportivo Barber|CSD Barber]] |caps2 = |goals2 = |years3 = 2007–2014 |clubs3 = [[RKSV Centro Dominguito|Centro Dominguito]] |caps3 = |goals3 = |years4 = 2014–2016 |clubs4 = [[Centro Social Deportivo Barber|CSD Barber]] |caps4 = |goals4 = |years5 = 2016– |clubs5 = [[RKSV Centro Dominguito|Centro Dominguito]] |caps5 = |goals5 = |nationalyears1 = 2005 |nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands Antilles national under-20 football team|Netherlands Antilles U20]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 1 |nationalyears2 = 2010 |nationalteam2 = [[Netherlands Antilles national football team|Netherlands Antilles]] |nationalcaps2 = 5 |nationalgoals2 = 1 |nationalyears3 = 2011 |nationalteam3 = [[Bonaire national football team|Bonaire]] |nationalcaps3 = 2 |nationalgoals3 = 2 |nationalyears4 = 2011–2015 |nationalteam4 = [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] |nationalcaps4 = 8 |nationalgoals4 = 0 |pcupdate = 21:11, 16 May 2017 (UTC) |ntupdate = 21:11, 16 May 2017 (UTC) }}
'''Kenneth Jesus Gregorio "Kenny" Kunst''' (born 1 November 1986) is a [[Curaçao]]n [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[RKSV Centro Dominguito|Centro Dominguito]].
==International career== Kunst originally played for the Netherlands Antilles,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caribbeannewsnow.com/sports.php?news_id=2737&start=0&category_id=8|title=Netherlands Antilles draw 2-2 with St Lucia in consolation tie of Caribbean Cup Group C|date=18 October 2010|accessdate=20 October 2016|work=Caribbean News Now}}</ref> playing 3 games for the Under 20 side in the preliminary qualification rounds at the [[2005 CONCACAF U-20 Tournament]] and scoring once.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/CONCACAF-U20-Men-20051.pdf|title=CONCACAF 2005 Under-20 Tournament Recap|date=1 June 2013|accessdate=20 October 2016|work=CONCACAF}}</ref> He played 5 games in total for the senior squad, scoring once against [[Guyana national football team|Guyana]] in a 3-2 defeat at the [[2010 Caribbean Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://caribbeanfootballdatabase.com/matches/2010/netherlandsantillesvsguyana10152010.html|title=Netherlands Antilles 2 - 3 Guyana|date=15 October 2010|accessdate=20 October 2016|work=CaribbeanFootballDatabase}}</ref>
When the Netherlands Antilles [[Dissolution of the Netherlands Antilles|dissolved]] in 2010, Kunst chose to represent Curaçao at international level. He made his début on the 20th August 2011 in a 1-0 friendly loss against the [[Dominican Republic national football team|Dominican Republic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://caribbeanfootballdatabase.com/matches/2011/dominicanrepublicvscuracao8202011.html|title=Dominican Republic 1 - 0 Curaçao|date=20 August 2011|accessdate=20 October 2016|work=CaribbeanFootballDatabase}}</ref>
Kunst has also represented the nation of [[Bonaire national football team|Bonaire]]. As Bonaire are not recognised by FIFA, any matches played are unofficial. He played two matches in the 2011 [[ABCS Tournament]], scoring both times. His goals came in a 3-1 victory over Curaçao<ref>{{cite web|url=http://caribbeanfootballdatabase.com/curacao/stories/curacaofalltobonaire1222011.html|title=Curaçao fall to Bonaire in ABCS|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=20 October 2016|work=CaribbeanFootballDatabase}}</ref> and in the final; a 2-2 draw with [[Aruba national football team|Aruba]], which Bonaire went on to win 4-3 on penalties.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://caribbeanfootballdatabase.com/aruba/stories/bonairewinabcs1242011.html|title=Bonaire win ABCS Tournament|date=4 December 2011|accessdate=20 October 2016|work=CaribbeanFootballDatabase}}</ref>
